## Files Found

- `/Users/shivam94/.pi/agent/extensions/orchestrator/activity-feed.ts` — spinner chars, render functions
- `/Users/shivam94/.pi/agent/extensions/orchestrator/subagent-runner.ts` — **contains the render timer for activity-feed**
- `/Users/shivam94/.pi/agent/extensions/orchestrator/plan-panel.ts` — spinner chars, own timer

## Key Code — activity-feed.ts spinner mechanism

```ts
// activity-feed.ts:24-25
const SPINNER_FRAMES = ["⠋", "⠙", "⠹", "⠸", "⠼", "⠴", "⠦", "⠧", "⠇", "⠏"];
let _spinnerIndex = 0;
```

Spinner index advanced **only inside render functions**:

```ts
// activity-feed.ts:105  (renderCombinedProgress)
_spinnerIndex++;

// activity-feed.ts:353  (renderActivityFeed)
_spinnerIndex++;
```

**No `setInterval` or timer in activity-feed.ts itself.** The render timing is external.

## Key Code — subagent-runner.ts (drives activity-feed rendering)

```ts
// subagent-runner.ts:171-179
let renderTimer: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;
const startRenderTimer = () => {
    renderTimer = setInterval(() => {
        if (feed.steps.length > 0 || output.length > 0) {
            const text = orchestratorActivity
                ? renderCombinedProgress(orchestratorActivity, specialist.name, feed, "")
                : renderActivityFeed(specialist.name, feed);
            onUpdate?.({ ... });
        }
    }, 1000);  // ← 1 SECOND interval
};
```

Also triggers render on: `tool_execution_start`, `tool_execution_end`, `message_end`.

## Key Code — plan-panel.ts spinner mechanism

```ts
// plan-panel.ts:17-18
const SPINNER_FRAMES = ["⠋", "⠙", "⠹", "⠸", "⠼", "⠴", "⠦", "⠧", "⠇", "⠏"];
let _spinnerIndex = 0;
```

**Two timers:**

```ts
// plan-panel.ts:130-146 — Spinner timer at 80ms
r.spinnerTimer = setInterval(() => {
    if (_reg().spinnerTimer !== r.spinnerTimer) { clearInterval(r.spinnerTimer!); return; }
    if (planState) {
        _spinnerIndex++;  // ← advances spinner
        _renderWidget();   // ← pushes to TUI
    } else { stopPlanTimer(); }
}, 80);  // ← 80 MILLISECONDS

// plan-panel.ts:147-162 — Elapsed timer at 1000ms
r.planTimer = setInterval(() => {
    if (_reg().planTimer !== r.planTimer) { clearInterval(r.planTimer!); return; }
    if (planState) {
        _renderWidget();  // ← updates elapsed time display
    } else { stopPlanTimer(); }
}, 1000);
```

## Key Code — plan-panel.ts cache (avoids redundant renders)

```ts
// plan-panel.ts:108-121
function _renderWidget(): void {
    if (!_setWidget) return;
    const lines = renderPlanLines();
    // Compare with cache — skip if nothing changed
    if (_lastWidgetContent && _lastWidgetContent.length === lines.length) {
        let same = true;
        for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
            if (_lastWidgetContent[i] !== lines[i]) { same = false; break; }
        }
        if (same) return;
    }
    _lastWidgetContent = lines;
    _setWidget(WIDGET_KEY, lines);
}
```

## Key Difference — Animation Speed

| Aspect | activity-feed (via subagent-runner) | plan-panel |
|--------|--------------------------------------|------------|
| **Spinner frame interval** | **1000 ms** | **80 ms** |
| Frames per second | 1 fps | 12.5 fps |
| Full cycle (10 frames) | 10 seconds | 0.8 seconds |
| Timer location | `subagent-runner.ts` (external) | `plan-panel.ts` (internal) |
| Render trigger | `onUpdate?.(...)` callback | `ctx.ui.setWidget()` |

**Root cause of slow activity-feed spinner:** The render timer in `subagent-runner.ts` fires every **1000ms**. Each call to `renderActivityFeed()` increments `_spinnerIndex` by 1 and returns rendered text. So spinner advances at 1 frame/second. plan-panel has a dedicated **80ms** interval that independently advances `_spinnerIndex` and calls `_renderWidget()`.

**Winner:** plan-panel spinner is **12.5x faster** (smooth animation). activity-feed spinner is **visibly sluggish** — one frame per second looks like it's barely moving.

**No throttle/debounce** in either file. activity-feed has no throttling because it doesn't have a timer (the slow rate is the entire problem). plan-panel has no throttling either — it runs at full 80ms speed with content dedup to avoid unnecessary re-layouts.

**No "fixed" version** or comment about slow spinner in either file.

